<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>have it good • have the worst of it</xh5><p> <i>have it good—</i>have enough money; be comfortably off: Mr. Goss said employers should realise that they <u>had it good</u> in Queensland compared with other states.</p><p> <i>have the worst of it—</i>1. suffer the most harm: We <u>had the worst of it</u> back there across the swamps—working up to our waists in water. 2. <i>(Sport)</i> be defeated: I would have <u>had the worst of it</u> in a sprint against Bettini, but I had the nerve against the other men.</p> </entry>
